        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 7:30PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne WY</headline>
        <description>At 730 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Crawford, or 23 miles southwest of Chadron, moving northeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Crawford, Soldier Creek Campground, and Fort Robinson State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
